4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROHIBITING ELECTIONEERING AT ALL POLLING LOCATIONS
5 FOR ALL ELECTIONS FROM THE TIME ABSENTEE BALLOTS ARE AVAILABLE UNTIL ALL VOTING IS
6 COMPLETED; PROVIDING AN EXCEPTION FOR COMMUNITY EVENTS AT WHICH ALL CANDIDATES
7 ARE INVITED; AMENDING SECTION 13-35-211, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE
8 DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 13-35-211, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "13-35-211. Electioneering -- soliciting information from electors -- exception. (1) A From the
14 start of in-person absentee voting as provided in 13-1-404, 13-1-503, 13-13-205, and 20-20-401, and until the
15 last person in line at a polling location on election day has voted or the polls close, whichever is later, a person
16 may not do any electioneering on election day within any polling place or any building in which an election is
17 being held or within 100 feet of any entrance to the building in which the polling place is located that aids or
18 promotes the success or defeat of any candidate or ballot issue to be voted upon on at the election, unless it is
19 a community event at which all candidates are invited.
20 (2) On election day, During the timeframe prescribed in subsection (1), a candidate, a family
21 member of a candidate, or a worker or volunteer for the candidate's campaign may not distribute alcohol,
22 tobacco, food, drink, or anything of value to a voter within a polling place or a building in which an election is
23 being held or within 100 feet of an entrance to the building in which the polling place is located, unless it is a
24 community event at which all candidates are invited.
25 (3) A person may not buy, sell, give, wear, or display at or about the polls on an election day
26 during the timeframe prescribed in subsection (1) any badge, button, or other insignia that is designed or tends
27 to aid or promote the success or defeat of any candidate or ballot issue to be voted upon on at the election.
